From 42a21c7ede94350d31e864f3f4961559dbb0d959 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Cristian Ciocaltea <cristian.ciocaltea@collabora.com>
Date: Sat, 7 Feb 2026 03:33:57 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 093/114] [WIP] video/hdmi: Add support for ALLM

Provide initial HF-VSIF support (including the HDMI 2.1 specific ALLM
feature) which passes the edid-decode compliance verification.

Additionally, add a dedicated DRM connector property named "allm enable"
that can be used to toggle ALLM on/off, assuming the sink advertises the
feature through its EDID.

Note there are still a bunch of TODOs remaining to be handled, it
remains to be seen if the current implementation is good enough to
successfully support running an end-2-end test.

Signed-off-by: Cristian Ciocaltea <cristian.ciocaltea@collabora.com>
